l materials on urban planning and policy, Peterson draws extensively on her own participation with Grand Performances, ranging from working in an information booth answering questions about the artists and the venue, to observing concerts and concert-goers as an audience member, to performing onstage herself as a cellist with the daKAH Hip Hop orchestra. The book offers an exploration of intersecting concerns of urban residents and scholars today that include social relations and diversity, public space and civic life, privatization and suburbanization and economic and cultural globalization.At a moment when cities around the world are undertaking similar efforts to revitalize their centers, Sound, Space, and the City conveys the underlying tensions of such projects and their relevance for understanding urban futures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity planningzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aSoundxSocial aspectszCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aUrban renewalzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 4aFolklore. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aAnthropology.  aFolklore.  aLinguistics.  aUrban Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Social Sciencesz978311041361808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220770540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812207705423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780812207705.jpg  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-